cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
title: "Continuous Architecture Assurance (CAA): Calibrating AI Reviewers as Instruments, Not Oracles"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Carvalho
    given-names: Rudson
abstract: >-
  An assurance layer for technical decisions that reframes AI-assisted
  architecture review as a metrology problem. AI reviewers are treated as
  instruments that emit measurements under a fixed verdict contract, gated by
  objective rules with mandatory traceability, and continuously calibrated
  against a corpus of real incidents using a paired recall / false-positive
  metric. Includes a reference specification (verdict contract) and a
  pre-registered falsification experiment.
keywords:
  - assurance case
  - software reliability
  - AI governance
  - calibration
  - metrology
  - LLM reviewers
  - architecture governance
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-06-26"
license: Apache-2.0
